# Power BI Service

## Introduction
Power BI Service is a cloud-based platform used to publish, share, and collaborate on Power BI reports and dashboards.

It enables organizations to access reports from anywhere using the internet.

---

## Features of Power BI Service

### 1. Report Publishing
- Upload Power BI Desktop reports (.pbix)
- Share with users or teams

### 2. Dashboards
- Combine visuals from multiple reports
- Real-time insights

### 3. Workspaces
- Collaborative environments for teams
- Organize reports and datasets

### 4. Data Refresh
- Scheduled refresh
- Automatic updates from data sources

### 5. Sharing & Collaboration
- Share dashboards with users
- Assign roles and permissions

---

## Power BI Service Workflow

1. Build report in Power BI Desktop
2. Publish to Power BI Service
3. Create dashboard
4. Share with users
5. Schedule data refresh

---

## Workspaces in Power BI
Workspaces are containers for:
- Reports
- Dashboards
- Datasets

### Types:
- My Workspace (Personal)
- Shared Workspaces (Team-based)

---

## Data Refresh Types
- Manual Refresh
- Scheduled Refresh
- Real-time Streaming

---

## Security in Power BI Service
- Role-based access
- Row-Level Security (RLS)
- Permissions control

---

## Advantages
- Cloud access from anywhere
- Easy collaboration
- Real-time reporting
- Centralized data management

---

## Limitations
- Requires internet
- Some features need premium license
- Data size limits in free version

---

## Key Takeaway
Power BI Service enables cloud-based sharing, collaboration, and real-time analytics for business users and organizations.
